Stage	Area	Topics to Cover	Tools / Libraries	Tools / Libraries
1	Programming Base	"Python fundamentals, functions, OOP, file handling"	Python	Python
2	Mathematics Foundation	"Vectors, matrices, derivatives, gradients, probability distributions, expectation"	"Linear Algebra, Probability Theory, Statistics, Calculus"	"Linear Algebra, Probability Theory, Statistics, Calculus"
3	Data Analysis	"Data cleaning, data visualization, data manipulation"	"NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib"	"NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib"
4	ML Workflow	"Data collection, preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, evaluation, deployment"	Python ecosystem	Python ecosystem
5	Supervised Learning	"Linear Regression, Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forest, Support Vector Machines, KNN, Naive Bayes"	Scikit-learn	Scikit-learn
6	Model Evaluation	"Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, Confusion Matrix, Cross-validation"	Scikit-learn tools	Scikit-learn tools
7	Unsupervised Learning	"K-Means Clustering, Hierarchical Clustering, DBSCAN, PCA"	Scikit-learn	Scikit-learn
8	Reinforcement Learning	"Agent, Environment, Reward, Policy, Value function, Q-learning, Deep Q Networks, Policy Gradient"	OpenAI Gym	OpenAI Gym
9	Deep Learning	"Neural Networks, CNN, RNN, Backpropagation"	"TensorFlow, PyTorch"	"TensorFlow, PyTorch"
10	Projects & Practice	"House price prediction, spam classifier, movie recommendation system, customer segmentation"	"Kaggle, UCI Machine Learning Repository"	"Kaggle, UCI Machine Learning Repository"
				
				
				
				
				
				
				
	Field	Top Elementary Topics to Know	Why It Matters in ML	
	Linear Algebra	"Vectors, vector operations, dot product"	Represents features and data points	
		"Matrices, matrix multiplication"	Used to store datasets and model parameters	
		Transpose of matrix	Used in many ML formulas	
		Matrix dimensions	Important for model computations	
		Eigenvalues & Eigenvectors (basic idea)	Used in PCA and dimensionality reduction	
	Calculus	Derivatives	Measure rate of change of loss function	
		Partial derivatives	Used when many variables exist	
		Gradient	Direction to minimize loss	
		Chain rule	Core idea behind backpropagation	
	Probability Theory	Random variables	Represent uncertain outcomes	
		Conditional probability	Used in classification models	
		Bayes theorem	Core idea of Naive Bayes classifier	
		Probability distributions	Understand data behavior	
	Statistics	Mean	Average of dataset	
		Variance	Data spread	
		Standard deviation	Measure variability	
		Normal distribution	Many ML assumptions follow this	
		Correlation	Relationship between features	
				
				
	Library	Topic	What You Need to Know	
	NumPy	Arrays	"Creating arrays, array shapes"	
		Indexing & Slicing	"Access specific elements, subarrays"	
		Mathematical Operations	"sum, mean, std, min, max"	
		Vectorized Operations	Element-wise operations without loops	
		Broadcasting	Operations on arrays of different shapes	
		Reshape & Transpose	"Reshape arrays, transpose matrices"	
		Random Number Generation	"randint, rand, normal, seed"	
	Pandas	DataFrames & Series	"Creating, accessing, modifying data"	
		Reading/Writing Data	"read_csv, read_excel, to_csv, to_excel"	
		Indexing & Selecting Data	"loc, iloc, boolean indexing"	
		Filtering Data	Conditions on columns	
		Handling Missing Values	"fillna(), dropna()"	
		GroupBy Operations	"groupby(), aggregate()"	
		Sorting & Ranking	"sort_values(), rank()"	
		Merging & Joining	"merge(), concat(), join()"	
		Feature Scaling	"min-max scaling, standardization"	
	Data Visualization (Basic)	Matplotlib Basics	"plot(), scatter(), hist(), bar()"	
		Customizing Plots	"title, xlabel, ylabel, legend"	
		Simple Insights	"trend lines, outliers"	
